            <me>
              \nabla^2A=\frac1r\pd{}{r}\left(r\pd{A}{r}\right)+\frac1{r^2}\pd{^2A}{\theta^2}+\pd{^2A}{z^2},
            </me>
            and <m>\bf=(f_r,f_\theta,f_z)</m> represents the body forces per unit mass
            acting on the fluid, which you may neglect in this question.
          </p>
          <p>
            Show that the flow
            <me>
              \bu=\left(0,\frac{a^2\Omega}{r},0\right)
            </me>
            satisfies the Navier<ndash/>Stokes equations and boundary conditions.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <!--<solution>
          <p>
            Since <m>u_r=u_z=0</m> and there is no <m>\theta</m>- or <m>z</m>-dependence,
